The paper discusses the latest trends in the field of evolutionary approaches to iris recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). It also discusses the establishment of an Interchange Protocol for Digital Identities, which involves security and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper presents experimental results and discusses the logical model of the protocol, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the power of discrimination achieved by the system, which involves information theory (cs.IT).
